<br>
I'm curious really, I always figured it was a waste of points. =| <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 8:49:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=80>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Alternate Advancement</span><hr size=1> Every person I have talked to who had maxed out Agility and Mitigation said it was extremely noticable.  I'm not certain how the formula works, but I have Agi1 and it didn't increase my AC.  I would tend to believe it's a separate check aside from AC to determine hit/miss, after the parry/dodge/riposte checks.  <br>
<br>
As for alternatives, what else is there for rogue archetypes? Durability is a definite 1 or 2 tier on your way to class skills.  But other than that, there really isn't much left.  Finishing blow is quite useless (there seems to be a level cap on it just like assassinate).  Fear resistance? someday.  Regen? someday.  The only immediate returns I saw were crits, but the current state of crit2 didn't impress me.  I'll see if I can coerce some guild rogues to parse out a log over the course of 1 night and compare crit1 to crit2 quantitatively.  <br>
<br>
Overall, I'd say the only things worth spending points on are crit1, and some combination of dura/miti/agi.  I made the mistake of putting 1 point in finishing blow, so I will most likely end up with crit1, dura1, agi2, finishing1 before moving on to chaoticstab.<br>
<br>
All of this is prelude to the real goal anyway: metabolism3 of course! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessageRange?topicID=8844.topic&start=141&stop=156>8</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showPrevMessage?topicID=8844.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showNextMessage?topicID=8844.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=80><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.emailToFriend?topicID=8844.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesa